---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { href } from '../../i18n/ui';

const email = 'raphael@plumservices.co';
const updated = '18 July 2026';
---

<Base
  lang="en"
  routeKey="privacy"
  title="Privacy policy — Sereno"
  description="What Sereno collects (very little), where data goes, Stripe voluntary support, and your rights — no AI processing of receipts."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
      <p>
        Sereno is a budgeting app: privacy isn’t fine print — it’s the product.
      </p>

      <h2>Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        Raphaël (publisher of Sereno, natural person) —
        <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Without an account: nothing leaves your device</h2>
      <p>
        In guest mode, all your data — transactions, accounts, budgets,
        categories, optional receipt photos — is stored
        <strong>only in your browser’s local storage</strong> (IndexedDB). It is
        not sent to any server. Receipt photos are
        <strong>never analyzed by AI</strong> or sent to an OCR service.
      </p>

      <h2>With an account: the minimum, in the EU</h2>
      <p>If you create an account (optional and free), we process:</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Email (and Google ID if you choose Google sign-in)</td>
            <td>Create and secure your account</td>
            <td>Contract performance (Terms)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Budget data (transactions, accounts, budgets, categories, recurring rules, receipts)</td>
            <td>Sync across your devices</td>
            <td>Contract performance (Terms)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        Stored at <strong>Supabase</strong> (EU, AWS eu-west-1), isolated per
        user (row-level security). The site is served by
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> (technical IP logs, legitimate interest).
      </p>

      <h2>Voluntary support (Stripe)</h2>
      <p>
        If you choose to support Sereno via a Stripe Payment Link, payment is
        processed by <strong>Stripe</strong>. Sereno does not store your card
        numbers. Stripe processes payment data under its own policy. This
        processing is based on performing the donation transaction you initiate.
      </p>
      <p>
        See also the <a href={href('en', 'support')}>Support</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2>What Sereno does not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No bank connection.</li>
        <li>No ads, no selling your data.</li>
        <li>No tracking cookies; no analytics tool at this time.</li>
        <li>No profiling, no automated decision-making, no AI processing of receipts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Guest mode:</strong> on your device, as long as you keep it.</li>
        <li><strong>Account:</strong> while the account exists, then deleted on request.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        GDPR rights of access, rectification, erasure, portability, restriction
        and objection: <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>. Export also
        available in-app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
